OL,3,CLeaders pressed on guaranteeing
OL,4,CStormont stability
OL,6,FThe leader of the official Opposition
OL,7,Fat Stormont Matthew O'Toole has
OL,8,Fwritten to First Minister Michelle
OL,9,FO'Neill and deputy First Minister Emma
OL,10,FLittle-Pengelly asking that they
OL,11,Fprovide a guarantee that neither will
OL,12,Fuse their position to collapse the
OL,13,Finstitutions.
OL,15,FMr O'Toole previously made the same
OL,16,Fcall on the floor of the Assembly.
OL,18,FHe has said he will keep making the
OL,19,Frequest until a commitment is made,
OL,20,Fsaying without it a question will
OL,21,Fremain over institutional stability.
