OL,3,CLeaders pressed on guaranteeing
OL,4,CStormont stability
OL,6,FIn his letter to the leaders, Mr
OL,7,FO'Toole said he wants to lead an
OL,8,FOpposition that is "positive,
OL,9,Fconstructive and focussed on the real
OL,10,Fchallenges facing people across
OL,11,FNorthern Ireland".
OL,13,FHe said only two people can collapse
OL,14,Fthe power-sharing government, adding:
OL,15,F"After all that we have endured over
OL,16,Fthe last two years, and over the three
OL,17,Fprevious years of abeyance, I am
OL,18,Fasking you again to provide a
OL,19,Fguarantee that you will not use your
OL,20,Fposition to collapse the Executive".
